—ЩKarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/commands/docs/mut.mdЩ@7021d5f8535922eba233996247db4e42a6c76308e5096ff060c3f126864df5c5Єtitle: mut‘ЁExamplesЪ·Set a mutable variable to a value, then update it.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> mut x = 10; $x = 12


```
Upsert a value inside a mutable data structure.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> mut a = {b:{c:1}}; $a.b.c = 2


```
Set a mutable variable to the result of an expression.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> mut x = 10 + 100


```
Set a mutable variable based on the condition.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> mut x = if false { -1 } else { 1 }


```
’ђђЪбTitle: title: mut
